name: A Siamese Dear Deer
description:
Watercolor and Pen in Paper
2021

Just like any other day, just like any of you, I spent a little too much time in the internet. I was looking for a deer picture and found out the news about a siamese twin deer. It’s interesting, I thought, so I opened it up.

I didn’t read the news, the picture was the only thing that intrigued me. Two head in a body and they just lay dead. Breathless.

I was wondering the details that leads them to the died. Was it because they had to share a body? Was it had conflicted interest? Or were they hate each other to the point they wanted to be separated?

I wish I know, but they can’t speak and dead and they are far away I assume. Just like we do, we are limited by how we are communicate and we might be gone faster than a blink.
